  "description": "The RDF Content Transformation Profile (the opt-in that makes a byte-native storage RDF-aware): capability/conformsTo consistency, the advertisement contract (an advertised pair is actually negotiable with Vary: Accept; RDF-aware clients feature-detect fail-closed — a profile-less ContentNegotiation entry makes no rdf-1 claim; a SparqlQueryService MUST NOT be advertised without the profile), graph-isomorphic source→target transformation with no inference and resource-URI base resolution, authoritative stored bytes with per-representation ETags + Vary: Accept + cross-representation If-Match, deterministic normalizes read-back, 406 degradation for unparseable sources, RDF PATCH formats scoped to the profile, and exact byte-native behaviour when the opt-in is off.",
